Since the death of king Zwelonke Sigcawu in 2019, the royal family has been divided on who should succeed him. President Ramaphosa issued a recognition certificate in February 2021 to Prince Ahlangene Sigcawu as the new monarch of the Amaxhosa Kingdom. Nceba Ntlanganiso has more. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Since the death of King Zwelonke Sigcawu in 2019, the royal family has been divided on who should succeed him. President Cyril Ramaphosa issued a recognition certificate in February 2021 to Prince Ahlangene Sigcawu as the new monarch of the Amaxhosa Kingdom. However, the other faction within the royal family says government did not consult them in that process. READ: Umembeso celebrations for AmaZulu royal family They say that they wrote letters to the Provincial Government up to the Presidency, opposing the recognition of the new King and were simply ignored. The other faction of the royal family which supports Prince Ahlangene Sigcawu disputes the claim that there was no consultation. They accuse some in the royal family of ulterior motives. A request for comment has been sent to COGTA. Watch the video above for more details on this story.